      <p>I believe that too much of the time most of us miss what is really happening. Too often we are half-consciously performing hackneyed caricatures received from sitcoms and advertisements. Dazed moments accumulate.</p>
      <p>If we step back to look at ourselves more consciously, we can notice the misalignment between our lives and our values. Pre-fabricated goals and absolutely uncreative forms of living determine our professional quests, our domestic projects, and our leisurely pursuits. Cookie cutters lop off the most quirky and delightful parts of ourselves.</p>
      <p>Exploring almost forgotten nooks and crannies of reality can help clear this desperate malaise. The grandeur of the universe spreads out immensely. We need only to notice it. The magnificence of ourselves rests deep within us. We need only attend to it. </p>
