      <p>As an explorer of ultimate reality, both within and without, I traverse the treasure stores of the human experience that are held in the texts of the Christian and Islamic traditions. I am no archaeologist. As fascinated as I am by the thoughts and discoveries of great souls and sharp minds from centuries past, my final focus is us here now. I traverse these forgotten stores to retrieve treasures of insight and possibility for us today.</p>
      <p>I am a theologian who constructs new meaning for us here now in conversation with sages of the past. My research is time travel. I am a comparative theologian who builds bridges of mutual understanding between Christians and Muslims and others who attend to Ultimate Reality. My writing begets solidarity and appreciation.</p>
      <p>I practice interreligious dialogue to make real and practical and present the vision I hold for mutual understanding and appreciation among members of different communities. I practice queer theology to re-think the body and the erotic, their meanings and their possibilities. </p>
